latestPosts.caption:
Nobody warned me about hormonal acne during the first trimester—it hit me hard and tested my patience. It wasn’t just about the physical discomfort but the emotional toll too. Battling breakouts while already dealing with gastritis and fatigue felt overwhelming. But I’ve learned to give myself grace and embrace this journey. Pregnancy skincare can be overwhelming but its best to speak to your gynac & dermatologist first before using anything given below💛 
A few products that helped me calm my skin down. 
• Azelaic acid ( Medical) 
• @glowrecipe Watermelon & niacinamide glow drops 
• @lamer moisturiser 
•  Clindac A (medical) 
• @isdin.india water based sunscreen
• @shangpree.official acne serum. 
 • @cetaphil_india gentle face wash 
• @cosrx snail mucin 
• @beminimalist__ Niacinamide

Navigating pregnancy-unsafe skincare felt like decoding a foreign language! Retinol, salicylic acid, AHA & BHAS shouldn’t be used. It’s all about protecting our little ones, the new adjustments can be overwhelming. Now, as my skin starts to feel like me again, I’m reminded that healing takes time, and that’s okay. Its the simple steps that help your skin, overloading your skin with products might back fire. More than anything I’m all ready for this new chapter🤎 

#FirstTrimesterStruggles #HormonalAcne #PregnancyJourney #Mamainthemaking
